div.p:
These Grogram rubbers are come in place of the See the form of them in Petronius Arbiter. ancient Strigiles or Scrapers: Not so much for the form or matter, for these rubbers are square, and serve only to cleanse away the filth that lyes in the skin, but the Strigiles were to scrape the skin: And certainly the former are much more commodious, and manageable, than those Instruments of Metal which had a handle and were made almost like a pruning hook. The Turks have the same liberty as to their Rubbers, which the Romans had in reference to their scrapers: For that every one may have his rubber to himself, and carry it with him to the Bath for his own particular use, and thus Crispin in Perseus sends for his own Scrapers;
I, puer, & strigiles Crispini ad balnea defer.
Go Boy, fetch Crispins scrapers to the Bath.
